ZH: 他每天来到办公室都会打招呼。
EN: He greets everyone when he arrives at the office every day.

ZH: 老板看见员工都会打招呼。
EN: The boss acknowledges the employees when he sees them.

ZH: 你一进门就要打招呼。
EN: You should greet people as soon as you enter.

ZH: 我喜欢和朋友打招呼。
EN: I like to say hello to my friends.

ZH: 每次见到他我都会打招呼。
EN: I always say hello to him whenever I see him.

ZH: 请你别忘了给我们打招呼。
EN: Please don't forget to greet us.

ZH: 你看到我也不打招呼？
EN: You didn't even greet me when you saw me?

ZH: 这是一个友好社区，人们都会互相打招呼。
EN: This is a friendly community where people greet each other.

ZH: 我们打招呼的方式会影响别人的印象。
EN: The way we greet others can make an impression on them.

ZH: 打招呼是一种文化习惯。
EN: Greeting is a cultural custom.

ZH: 他遇到陌生人也会打招呼。
EN: He greets strangers as well.

ZH: 在中国，打招呼通常包括握手。
EN: In China, greetings usually involve shaking hands.

ZH: 打招呼是互相尊重和友好的表现。
EN: Greeting is a way to show mutual respect and friendliness.

ZH: 我们之间没有必要打招呼。
EN: There's no need for us to greet each other.

ZH: 请你先去给客人打招呼。
EN: Please go greet the guests first.

ZH: 和同事打招呼是建立良好关系的一部分。
EN: Greeting colleagues is a part of building good relationships.

ZH: 他太自大了，从不主动打招呼。
EN: He's too arrogant to greet others first.

ZH: 我们终于打招呼了，很开心见到他。
EN: We finally greeted each other and were happy to see him.

ZH: 我们要向所有老师打招呼。
EN: We need to greet all the teachers.

ZH: 在这个乡村，人们都会热情地打招呼。
EN: In this village, people greet each other warmly.
